CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 6, 1955, pg. 11 reads: "Breakfast on the Lawn - Min-Ceil Club breakfast, held on the spacious lawn of the Emmett F. Davises of Lincoln Avenue, as usual was a scene of beauty last Sunday, when hundreds of fashionable socialites attended the annual outdoor affair. Here you see just a partial picture of the crowd which enjoyed a sumptuous breakfast and the wholesome fun of chatting with old and new friends at the event.- "Teenie" Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Crowd of women, and men, one in foreground wearing moustache and diagonally striped necktie, pouring drink from pitcher, on lawn of Emmett F. Davises home for the Min-Ceil Club breakfast
